<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Learn about Cassie, a community-focused CPR and first aid trainer."
	heroImage="/cassie.jpg"
>
	<p> 
		Hi, I’m Cassie <i>(she/they)</i>. I run Cassie’s Practice Resuscitation Training, where I teach CPR and first aid in a way that’s approachable and easy to follow. Whether you just need to renew your certificate or want more hands-on practice to feel confident, I’ve got options to suit. </p> 
	<p> 
		My aim is simple: help people feel ready to step in during an emergency. I keep sessions low-cost (or pay-what-you-can) and create a relaxed, supportive environment — no intimidating classroom vibes. As a trans person, creating a space that feels safe, respectful, and inclusive, especially for LGBTQIA+ folks, is an important part of how I run sessions.</p> 
	<p> 
		I’ve worked across healthcare, outdoor education, and emergency response including as a first aid trainer, ski and mountain bike patroller, and outdoor educator. That mix means I bring real-world scenarios and practical skills into every session. </p> 
	<h2>My Values</h2> 
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Inclusive:</strong> A space where people of all backgrounds can learn safely and confidently.
		</li> 
		<li>
			<strong>Practical:</strong> Hands-on sessions that help skills stick.
		</li> 
		<li>
			<strong>Community-focused:</strong> Supporting local groups and people who might not otherwise have access.
		</li> 
	</ul> 
	<p> 
		If you’d like me to run a session for you, your workplace, or a community group, feel free to <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>. 
	</p>
</Layout>